{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f7611da6-b6e5-4de4-beee-db103e5cd1dc","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types from files listed **above** them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing by reordering:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01GbP8PMQe972bY6LAP7dysG","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-9aaad43fde6e4278af5f951caa9df1bc/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-9aaad43fde6e4278af5f951caa9df1bc/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"8421ac35-f944-4bd7-be28-3288949e6b8a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear **earlier** in the compilation order. \n\nIn the `.fsproj`, the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — references `BrokenOrder.Domain` (but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet!)\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — references both\n\nThe fix is to reorder so `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":379,"requestId":"7C11:27C689:A99206:C1F5A6:6A02792A"},"id":"69effd87-d7ee-469b-97a3-f858a45402bf","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:49:55.684Z","parentId":"e7567bc2-7298-44f2-a5a6-355d6fbff1d4"}
